                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6176: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-14T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 14, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 14—5:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>330. Yoshizawa<note n="90" xml:id="d288fn90">Kenkichi Yoshizawa, member Japanese
                        House of Peers.</note> visited Peiping. I am informed that he was not able
                    to see any Chinese of importance here or in the South. I believe purpose of his
                    visit was to inform himself of current Chinese reactions to Japanese occupation
                    of Jehol and activities along Wall. He left impressed with fact that for the
                    time being no Chinese are prepared to commit themselves to negotiations direct
                    or indirect. I believe that he expects a change of government in May or at
                    latest in July and that Seiyukai<note n="91" xml:id="d288fn91">Seiyukai
                        Party.</note> will succeed present government and that he will be Minister
                    of Foreign Affairs. He was accompanied by Count Iwaki of the House of Peers and
                    Mr. Hashimoto of the Diet.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
